his station is the first stop in [[Pudong]] going east towards [[Pudong International Airport]], and is part of the initial section of Line 2 that opened from {{SHM stations|Zhongshan Park}} to {{SHM stations|Longyang Road}} that opened on 20 September 1999.<ref name=\"\u4e0a\u6d77\u5e74\u92742000\u5341\u56db\">{{cite web|url=http://shtong.gov.cn/node2/node19828/node20062/node20083/node64318/userobject1ai67955.html |script-title=zh:\u4e0a\u6d77\u5e02\u5730\u65b9\u5fd7\u529e\u516c\u5ba4 \u4e0a\u6d77\u901a\u7f51\u7ad9 \u4e0a\u6d77\u5e02\u5730\u60c5\u8d44\u6599\u5e93 \u4e0a\u6d77\u5e02\u7684\u767e\u79d1\u5168\u4e66 |website=shtong.gov.cn|accessdate=13 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"\u4e0a\u6d77\u5e74\u92742000\u4e8c\u5341\u516d\">{{cite web|url=http://shtong.gov.cn/node2/node19828/node20062/node20093/node64347/userobject1ai68070.html |script-title=zh:\u4e0a\u6d77\u5e02\u5730\u65b9\u5fd7\u529e\u516c\u5ba4 \u4e0a\u6d77\u901a\u7f51\u7ad9 \u4e0a\u6d77\u5e02\u5730\u60c5\u8d44\u6599\u5e93 \u4e0a\u6d77\u5e02\u7684\u767e\u79d1\u5168\u4e66 |website=shtong.gov.cn|accessdate=13 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"firstline\">{{cite news|url=http://sh.eastday.com/m/20130527/u1a7417946.html|date=27 May 2013|newspaper=Eastday|language=Chinese|script-title=zh:20\u5e74\u8fc8\u5411\u4e16\u754c\uff1a\u73cd\u8d35\u8001\u7167\u7247\u5c55\u793a\u4e0a\u6d77\u5730\u94c1\u53d1\u5c55|accessdate=14 July 2013}}</ref> Being at the centre of Lujiazui, the station is of significance to the area.\n\n==Location==\nLujiazui station is located in the [[Lujiazui|financial district of the same name]] near the eastern bank of the [[Huangpu River]]. Located at the major intersection of [[Century Avenue]], Fenghe Road, Lujiazui West Road, and Lujiazui Ring Road, the station is within reach of many famous attractions in Shanghai. To the northwest is the [[Oriental Pearl Tower]], [[Shanghai IFC]] lies to the immediate south, and [[Super Brand Mall]] lies to the southwest. Further afield, the [[Jin Mao Tower]] and [[Shanghai World Financial Center]] lie to the southeast, the latter of which is equidistant between Lujiazui and {{SHM stations|Dongchang Road}} stations.<ref name=\"map\">[http://www.shmetro.com/node155/node157/201004/con103668.htm Lujiazui area map] ''Shanghai Metro'' Retrieved 1 August 2010</ref> A number of parks, including Lujiazui Central Green, are within a few minutes' walk from the station as well.\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:Lujiazui metro station.jpg|Station platform\nFile:201604 AC08-233 enters Lujiazui Station.JPG|An AC08 train enters this station\nFile:201805 Exit 3 of Lujiazui Station.jpg|Exit 3 of this station\nFile:Lujiazui Station Line 2 Platform.jpg|Station platform\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Pudong}}\n{{Shanghai Metro\n|line2=yes\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Shanghai Metro stations in Pudong]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1999]]\n[[Category:1999 establishments in China]]\n[[Category:Line 2, Shanghai Metro]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Shanghai]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Shanghai Metro station}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2010}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name             = Lujiazui\n| native_name      = \u9646\u5bb6\u5634\n| native_name_lang = zh-Hans\n| symbol_location  = shanghai\n| symbol           = metro\n| symbol_location2 = \n| symbol2          = \n| symbol_location3 = \n| symbol3          = \n| symbol_location4 = \n| symbol4          = \n| image            = 201805 Exit 4 of Lujiazui Station.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Station exit 4 at night in May 2018\n| mlanguage        = <!-- Template:Infobox Chinese/Chinese -->\n| other_name       = \n| address          = [[Century Avenue]] and Middle Yincheng Road ({{nowrap|{{lang|zh-hans|\u94f6\u57ce\u4e2d\u8def}}}})\n| borough          = [[Lujiazui]], [[Pudong]], [[Shanghai]]\n| country = China\n| map_type = China Shanghai\n| map_caption = Location in Shanghai\n| map_size = \n| coordinates      = {{coord|31